hip of Ireland in 1002."],"variants":[{"name":"O'Brion","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Bryon","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish William Kevin.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"Bryan","meanings":["English and Irish: variant of   Bryant  .","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of <b>Ó Briain</b>, see   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Briant","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  , with excrescent <i>-t</i>."]},{"name":"O'Bryant","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"McBrien","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Seamus.","Irish:","Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Briain</b> ‘son of Brian’. See   O'Brien   and   Bryan  ."]},{"name":"O'Brian","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Liam.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Bryan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish James Patrick, Padraic.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]}]},{"name":"Maria","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Maria  , of German origin but now also moderately popular in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Maria O'Brien was born in 1362, in Ely Lodge, County Fermanagh, Northern Ireland, United Kingdom. She married Turlogh O'Brien Bishop Killloe in 1382, in Leinster, Ireland. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1420, in her hometown, at the age of 58."},"et":{"1362–1420":"1362–1420","1353–1428":"1353–1428","1370–1395":"1370–1395","1401–Male":"1401–Surnud","Abt 1370":"umbes 1370","1401":"1401","1420":"1420","1353":"1353","1362":"1362","1395":"1395","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1428":"1428","Arragh More, Tipperary, Munster, Ireland":"Arragh More, County Tipperary, Iirimaa","Leinster, Ireland, United Kingdom":"Ireland, Orkney, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Parsonstown, County Offaly, Ireland, United Kingdom":"Parsonstown, Coun